## Justice's Biotech Brief — 2026-06-18 — published

**Pick:** LRRC15 cryo-EM structure paper (Walter and Eliza Hall Institute, Shakeel lab — bioRxiv 10.64898/2026.06.16.732218, posted 2026-06-18). First high-resolution structure (2.6 Å) of LRRC15 in complex with samrotamab vedotin (ABBV-085), the LRRC15-targeting ADC AbbVie advanced into Phase 1 in sarcoma before shelving it. Shows samrotamab binds laterally on the C-terminal membrane-proximal LRRs, leaving the canonical concave face fully exposed; authors then computationally designed de novo minibinders targeting that concave face with multiple nanomolar hits. Translational signal for an ADC-focused immunologist: LRRC15 has a structurally distinct second surface nobody has touched — non-overlapping epitope, no IP collision with samrotamab estate, and an obvious trispecific TCE play (tumor antigen × CD3 × concave-face LRRC15) to bridge T cells to desmoplastic stroma.

**Commit:** `0058400`. mp3 published to R2 (2,176,566 bytes, 272 s / 4:32). Feed XML validated (`xml.etree.ElementTree` parse OK).

