**Justice's Biotech Brief — 2026-06-25**

**Selected:** Widdess et al., *Bispecific Antibody Architecture and TNFRSF Target Selection Determine CD8+ T Cell Differentiation and Anti-tumour Immunity*, bioRxiv 10.64898/2026.06.19.732642 v1 (posted June 24, 2026). Al-Shamkhani / Cragg / Beers, University of Southampton.

**Why it wins:** Architecture-rules paper for the costim bispecific space. Quantifies (1) format effect — 2x2 max, 1x1 min, asymmetric 2x1 retains substantial activity, identifying costim-receptor bivalency (not tumor-antigen bivalency) as load-bearing; (2) receptor effect — 4-1BB beats other TNFRSF members, hierarchy conserved in human T cells and reproduced by cognate ligand, so receptor-intrinsic. Lands directly on the AbCellera-Jazz costim trispecific deal Justice's brief covered six days ago.

