**Why this pick beat the others:** the EV-303 readout is the first regulatory data set authorizing an ADC + PD-1 inhibitor in a curative-intent perioperative setting — a 48-percentage-point pCR delta and 50% OS reduction. It sits at the exact intersection of Justice's ADC and immunotherapy interests, and resets the proof point every other ADC + checkpoint combination program (datopotamab deruxtecan, sacituzumab govitecan, HER3 D-X-d, CEACAM5, Claudin-18.2) will be measured against when moving into earlier lines.

