**Pick**: Chung, Ozcelik, Zhang, ... Beyaz (CSHL + MIT Fox microbiome lab + Univ. Pittsburgh Hand lab), *Microbial induction of MHC-II expression in colon cancer cells overcomes immunotherapy resistance and limits metastasis*, bioRxiv 2026.06.30.735621 (posted 2026-07-04). A defined Helicobacter community induces tumor-intrinsic CIITA → MHC class II → converts MSS colorectal cancer (AKPS orthotopic model + human MSS PDOs) from checkpoint-refractory to a 71% complete-rejection rate under PD-1 + CTLA-4 (vs 10% in Helicobacter-negative controls). Necessary+sufficient tumor-intrinsic MHC-II is the newly druggable target one step upstream of the microbiome itself.

**Candidate funnel**:

- bioRxiv 2026-07-04 → 2026-07-05 (details API, full 59-paper corpus, both pages): 3 on-beat matches after keyword filter (VEGF/PD-L1/PD-1/TCE/bispecific/CAR-T/ADC/JAK/checkpoint/immunotherapy).
